## Listing Sites

> Example Request

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->get("sites");
?>
```

> Example Response

<% json do %>
{
  "sites": [
    <%= print_json(data.objects['site'], :minimal => true) %>,
    <%= print_json(data.objects['site'], :minimal => true, :include => {
      'id' => 4,
      'name' => 'Lone Pine'
    }) %>
  ]
}
<% end %>

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites`



## Get Existing Site

> Example Request

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/9 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```
```php
<?php
$wiw = new Wheniwork("<%=@wiw_token%>");
$result = $wiw->get("sites/9");
?>
```

> Example Response

<% json do %>
{
  "site": <%= print_json(data.objects['site'], :minimal => true) %>
}
<% end %>

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/{id}`

### Parameters

Key | Description
--- | -----------
id | ID of the site requested.


## Create/Update Site

### Create HTTP Request
`POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/`

### Update HTTP Requests
`PUT <%=@api_prefix%>/2/sites/{id}`

### Parameters

The `POST` or `PUT` body can include fields from the [Site Object](#sites).


